{"ts":"2026-04-07T09:27:52.060Z","tool":"execute_code","type":"tool","status":"ERROR","ms":12141,"action":"execute","params":{"action":"execute","code":"\n// Fix 1: Move player to an open area (not inside a building)\nvar player = GameObject.Find(\"Player\");\nvar terrain = Terrain.activeTerrain;\nVector3 vc = new Vector3(-375f, 0f, 625f);\n\n// Place player at village center, elevated\nfloat groundY = terrain.SampleHeight(vc) + terrain.transform.position.y;\nplayer.transform.position = new Vector3(vc.x, groundY + 1f, vc.z - 30f);\n\n// Fix 2: Check minimap camera - needs correct culling and layers\n// The minimap camera should see terrain and buildings but might be culling wrong\nvar result = $\"Player moved to {player.transform.position}\\n\";\n\n// Fix 3: Check if the minimap RenderTexture is being created\n// The GameHUD creates it at runtime, but let's verify the camera layer setup\nvar allCams = GameObject.FindObjectsOfType<UnityEngine.Camera>(true);\nresult += $\"Cameras in scene: {allCams.Length}\\n\";\nforeach (var cam in allCams)\n{\n    result += $\"  {cam.gameObject.name}: depth={cam.depth} ortho={cam.orthographic} culling={cam.cullingMask}\\n\";\n}\n\n// Check that the Main Camera is correct\nvar mainCam = GameObject.Find(\"Main Camera\");\nif (mainCam != null)\n{\n    var cam = mainCam.GetComponent<UnityEngine.Camera>();\n    if (cam != null)\n    {\n        result += $\"\\nMain Camera tag: {mainCam.tag}\\n\";\n        if (mainCam.tag != \"MainCamera\")\n        {\n            mainCam.tag = \"MainCamera\";\n            result += \"  Fixed tag to MainCamera\\n\";\n        }\n    }\n}\n\n// Save\nUnityEditor.SceneManagement.EditorSceneManager.MarkSceneDirty(\n    UnityEditor.SceneManagement.EditorSceneManager.GetActiveScene());\nUnityEditor.SceneManagement.EditorSceneManager.SaveOpenScenes();\n\nreturn result;\n","safety_checks":true,"compiler":"auto"},"error":"Runtime error: Object reference not set to an instance of an object"}
